Description:
Cyber GRC Analyst
A leading healthcare provider is looking at building their Security Team with an Analyst in their Governance, Risk and Compliance team.
You will be working with internal stakeholders and have a decent understanding of cyber security risk management, governance, policy and process. You’ll be the voice of security working on advisory projects and working closely with the broader GRC team. You could come from a technical background, advisory or consulting background with passion to make your mark in the world of Security.
Core skills:

Awareness of security standards such as ISO27001, NIST or PCI-DSS
Knowledge of risk management methodologies;
Security policy and procedure writing knowledge or experience as they relate to core security artefacts defined in a security framework;
An interest in business and technical areas in the development of security controls and documentation in preparation for an external audit;
Experience or understanding of developing technical documentation;
An understanding of information security tools such as SIEM, EPP, IPS, IDS and GRC Products;
Support accreditation and compliance activities.

Please call russell on 0438984265 / russell@theonset.com.au

As a Consultant, Protective Security, you will support and contribute to the deployment and operation of NAB’s Physical Security policies and procedures focusing on protective and physical security operations. 
You will have the opportunity to:
Apply relevant specialist knowledge and experience to understand, influence and advise internal and/or external clients in relation to physical security matters. Day to day you will:
• Support the Manager of Protective Security, to provide security advice and guidance to employees relating to executive protection, travel security, physical security incidents and event security;
• Provide support and guidance to the Physical Security Operations Centre for operational security matters and critical incidents, including periods of on-call;
• Lead intelligence gathering, interrogate information systems and open-source data, to conduct threat assessments and understand the security environment;
• Review data relating to security incidents, develop responses to trends, and proactively contribute to process development and improvement;
• Identify, evaluate and monitor risks that could affect business activities and provide timely insight and information to assist decision making; and
• Conduct security risk assessments and apply controls to mitigate identified risks.
Functions, including the use of discretion/delegation and authority may be carried out within clearly defined policies, principles and specific objectives and may include people leadership roles with leadership accountability for a team, or teams, of employees. Employees are responsible for the delivery of work, but accountability may sit at a higher Group.
This role has shared responsibility to cross skill with other team members to eliminate key person risk to ensure continuity of service as Physical Security delivers Critical A processes. Tasks include data collection and analysis, reporting and risk assessment coordination, real time security incident management, participating in internal and external led forums.
Your skills and experience:
•        Proven (5 + years) experience in incident management, risk management, intelligence, or protective security;
•            Understanding of law enforcement processes and the ability to liaise with law enforcement;
•            Proven experience in conducting security risk and threat assessments and a thorough understanding of risk assessment standards and methodology;
•            An understanding of the international security environment, protecting travellers internationally, and impacts of international security incidents on NAB;
•            Experience in providing guidance on personal safety, workplace, family or domestic violence situations; and
•            Relevant qualifications in security, risk management and/or industry accreditations desired.
*Please note unsolicited CVs from agencies will not be accepted.
To help keep our community safe, candidates are required to comply with vaccine requirements outlined in state based public health orders.
